1.TX: Kyen wears an ornate sand hourglass around her neck via a sinew string. It seems to still be one-hundred percent functional.

2.TX: Despite Kyen's claims of being older than she'd care to admit, she doesn't really appear to be much older than a young adult highborne.

3.TX:
Kyenthis is definitely a gifted magic user, as those magically inclined will have no issues sensing a powerful arcane aura around her. 

There appears to be another aura there, but its hidden.

4.TX: Kyen's hair, which reaches to her knees, never seems to lose its length for more than a day even when cut. Whether or not this is related to her mastery of magic is uncertain, but it certainly is a bit odd..

5.TX:
If you have ever felt alone, suicidal, hopeless, lost, worthless, abandoned, scared, or ANYTHING of that nature! Any of it, even for a second! 

Read this. Out loud. Riiiiiight now.

You are beautiful.
You are wanted.
You are wonderful.
You are loved.
Your life is worth living.
Your life is valued.
Your life is sacred.
Your life is unique.

Done? Do it again, at least another nine times. Trust me, it can help.

Don't quit on yourself. Don't hurt yourself. You are worth the world and no one wants to actually see you suffering, no matter how much it may seem those odds are against you. This is not the end. The way you feel right now can and will pass, I assure you. 

People's minds can and will change. Things can and WILL get better.

DO NOT DO SOMETHING PERMANENT OVER SOMETHING TEMPORARY, NO MATTER HOW BAD IT GETS.

You're better than that.

If nobody has told you today-- no, even if they have-- you're awesome and I love you.

I am always here to lend an ear or a fluffy hug in the span of mere seconds, do not forget this. Even if I look busy, if you need somebody to talk with, hit me up with a whisper.

I have been in your shoes one too many times before, and if there is one thing I have learned...you don't have to go through it alone.

MI.VA: "You're never too old to learn something new."
